    <!--  Dragon Tamer Class  -->
    <element name="Dragon Tamer" type="Class" source="Worlds Collide" id="ID_WC_CLASS_DRAGON_TAMER">
        <description>
            <p>A Human finds a dragon egg in the wild, abandoned and left to its own devices. The egg is warm to the touch and seems to pulse with a faint inner light. It hatches and looks at the human. The human leaves it alone, but it follows him around. Eventually the human picks up the baby dragon and takes it with him on his adventures. The dragon grows with the human and they become partners, taking on everything together.</p>
            <h3>CLASS FEATURES</h3>
            <p>As a Dragon Tamer, you have the following class features.</p>
            <h5>HIT POINTS</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li>
                    <strong>Hit Dice:</strong>
                    1d10 per Dragon Tamer level
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Hit Points at 1st Level:</strong>
                    10 + your Constitution modifier
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Hit Points at Higher Levels:</strong>
                    1d10 (or 6) + your Constitution modifier per Dragon Tamer level after 1st
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h5>PROFICIENCIES</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled mb">
                <li>
                    <strong>Armor:</strong>
                    none
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Weapons:</strong>
                    Simple weapons
                </li>
                <li>
                <strong>Tools:</strong>
                    None
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li>
                    <strong>Saving Throws:</strong>
                    Strength, Dexterity
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Skills:</strong>
                    Choose three from Athletics, Survival, Stealth, Investigation, Nature, Animal Handling, Insight, or Perception
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h5>EQUIPMENT</h5>
            <p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>one shortbow and 20 arrows</li>
                <li>one dagger</li>
                <li>(a) a dungeoneer's pack or (b) an explorer's pack</li>
            </ul>
